{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h3 id=\"1-build-design-systems\"><a href=\"#1-build-design-systems\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>1. Build design systems</h3>\n<p>I love to build scalable design systems from the ground up such as the work I did for <a href=\"/hellocar\">Hellocar</a>.This is importnat to me because you start with the bare building blocks of an experience and you build upon it. Making a system that scales as the product grows.</p>\n<h3 id=\"2-multi-disciplined-team\"><a href=\"#2-multi-disciplined-team\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>2. Multi-disciplined team</h3>\n<p>The success or the failure of a product never comes down to if you had the best designer or the best developer. It comes down to how the team works together and delivers the product and this was true with the team in <a href=\"/Laterooms\">LateRooms</a>. I am not a big fan of waterfalls. üöø ‚òπÔ∏è</p>\n<h3 id=\"2-experiments-and-validation\"><a href=\"#2-experiments-and-validation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>2. Experiments and Validation</h3>\n<p>I believe getting something in front of users helps to validate ideas quickly and cheaply but I also believe this gives you the chance to be bold and challenging. A good example is a work I did for <a href=\"/cambrdige-audio\">Cambridge Audio.</a>.</p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/approach","title":"HOW I WANT WORK","templateKey":"approach"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"55138d9b-5cd6-5817-b3ee-6aaa9abfd25f"}}